The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on restoring the correct case of characters in textual data. This falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed architecture uses deep learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks (cs.CV), bi-directional long short-term memory networks (cs.NE), and conditional random fields (cs.LG) to achieve the task. The paper also mentions that their approach does not require explicit feature engineering, which is a common characteristic of machine learning algorithms (cs.AI).
